HEADWORD: Mistrial
<hw>Mis*tri"al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A
false or erroneous trial; a trial which has no result; a trial which
comes to no conclusion, such as a criminal trial which does not produce
a unanimous verdict of the jurors.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mistrist</ent>⟦br⟧
